  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , we already laid down the set-up of bipartite graphs for all genera. It is natural to expect higher genus graphs lead to higher genus relative Gromov-Witten cycles. However, at that time we still made genus-0 restrictions on the bipartite graphs in the main results because no evidence was found to justify the usefulness of the higher genus generalization. In this paper, we aim to present a small progress in the higher genus generalization. The main point of this paper can be summarized as follows:",
